\nstrategy or ionospheric effects. On the timescale of one year we find two\nsources that show significant variability. We attribute this variability to\neither refractive scintillation or intrinsic variability. No radio transients\nwere identified and we place an upper limit on the surface density of sources\nrho < 7.5 x 10^-5 deg^-2 with flux densities > 5.5 Jy, and characteristic\ntimescales of both 26 minutes and one year.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Nov 2013 00:26:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
