{"id":"1411.7304","submitter":"Alexey Burov","authors":"Alexey Burov and Lev Burov","title":"Genesis of a Pythagorean Universe","comments":"10 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.hist-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The full-blown multiverse hypothesis, chaosogenesis, is refuted on the\ngrounds of the large scale and high precision of the already discovered laws of\nnature. A selection principle is required not only to explain the possibility\nof life and consciousness, but also theoretizability of our universe. The weak\nanthropic principle provides the former, but not the latter. As chaosogenesis\nis shown to be the only thinkable scientific answer to the question of why the\nlaws of nature are the way they are, its refutation means that this question\ncannot be answered scientifically.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Nov 2013 04:58:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Nov 2014 02:43:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 7 Jul 2015 03:31:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-08"}
